"Eye Galaxy".
What makes an image realistic, and why?

Macro photos of the iris have always fascinated me. A micro galaxy full of mysterious textures looming into this eye exam question in what makes an image realistic vs digital vs illustrative?

This micro world exists, but most have never seen it, hence seemingly unreal. I might go into the atom level but how am I to know what is real when I have never seen it? Maybe it all looks like neon cyberpunk cartoons in reality.

What makes an image more realistic? What cues, hints, distractions, assumptions, imperfections, triggers, perceptions, etc. 

Why does it even matter?
